SIMPLE: manly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manly
<hw>Man"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Manlier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Manliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[<ets>Man</ets> + <ets>-ly</ets>.
Cf. <er>Manlike</er>.]</ety> <def>Having qualities becoming to a man;
not childish or womanish; manlike, esp. brave, courageous, resolute,
noble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let's briefly put on <qex>manly</qex> readiness.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Serene and <qex>manly</qex>, hardened to sustain⟦br⟧
The load of life.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Bold; daring; brave; courageous; firm; undaunted;
hardy; dignified; stately.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Manly
<hw>Man"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a manly manner; with the
courage and fortitude of a manly man; <as>as, to act
<ex>manly</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>man-made</ent>⟦br⟧
